PREQUEL — WORLD MECHANICS: REALM OF SHADS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

THE REALM OF SHADS
  A dimension separate from the human world (Earth). It is home to beings
  called Sonapers — entities that share the characteristics of human
  personality but have no tangible physical form.

SONAPERS
  Non-physical beings. Their personalities mirror human archetypes (combat
  hunger, domain mastery, defence, manipulation, etc.) but they cannot
  interact with the material world on their own. Powers remain dormant
  unless the Sonaper holds the title of Revis.

REVIS
  The highest position among Sonapers. The Sonaper who attains Revis has
  their powers fully unlocked. Only one (or a select group) can hold this
  title at a time. The Revis can be challenged and replaced.

THE COMPETITION (held every century)
  1. Sonapers who wish to challenge for Revis are gathered in the Realm of Shads.
  2. They undergo the ritual of SHOSHINSHA — a transformation that converts
     each Sonaper into a physical card.
  3. Upon transformation, each card attains a colour. Colours represent the
     5 power levels — a Sonaper's proximity to becoming Revis:
       Lvl 1  →  Lvl 2  →  Lvl 3  →  Lvl 4  →  Lvl 5 (Revis)
     [Current document covers Lvl 3 participants only]
  4. The cards (Shoshinsha) are taken out of the Realm of Shads into Earth.
  5. Cards spread across the world. Each card is drawn automatically toward
     a human whose aura matches the Sonaper's personality. The card bonds to
     that human — granting them the Sonaper's power set.
  6. The competition then unfolds among the bonded humans on Earth.

HOW SUITS MAP TO PERSONALITY COLOURS
  ♣ Clubs / Leaves  →  Raw combat hunger, brute power drive
  ♠ Spades          →  Domain mastery, discipline, realm-seeking ambition
  ♥ Hearts          →  Balance of offence and defence, protective instinct
  ♦ Diamonds        →  Intelligence, manipulation, betrayal, self-interest

OUTSIDE CARD STRUCTURE
  Some Sonapers participated in past competitions but are no longer active
  contestants. They exist in the realm as retired or defeated legends.
  Their cards are no longer in circulation on Earth.

